<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,310,701,727]" box="[189,310,701,727]" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,701,727]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="86" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,701,727]" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[187,1399,748,916]" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Miller &amp; Buchar, 1977" authorityName="Miller &amp; Buchar" authorityYear="1977" box="[564,1030,748,774]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bohemicus">
<emphasis box="[564,733,748,774]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">H. bohemicus</emphasis>
Miller &amp; Buchar, 1977
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[1046,1393,748,774]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concertor">
<emphasis box="[1046,1202,749,774]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">H. concertor</emphasis>
(Simon, 1878)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bosmans &amp; Abrous, 2018" authorityName="Bosmans &amp; Abrous" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,630,784,810]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="securifer">
<emphasis box="[189,326,784,810]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">H. securifer</emphasis>
Bosmans &amp; Abrous, 2018
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Marusik, Hippa &amp; Koponen, 1996" authorityName="Marusik, Hippa &amp; Koponen" authorityYear="1996" box="[639,1243,783,810]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudosignifer">
<emphasis box="[639,845,784,810]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">H. pseudosignifer</emphasis>
Marusik, Hippa &amp; Koponen, 1996
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Thaler, 1984" authorityName="Thaler" authorityYear="1984" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenus">
<emphasis box="[1295,1399,784,809]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">H. aenus</emphasis>
Thaler, 1984
</taxonomicName>
by having a relatively thin embolic apophysis (
<emphasis box="[882,915,820,845]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">Ea</emphasis>
) with smooth surface/edges and by being over 2.5 times as long as wide but differs from them by having a prolateral bulge on the bulb (
<emphasis box="[1248,1280,854,880]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">Bb</emphasis>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[188,231,1363,1389]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,269,1323]" captionTargetId="figure-92@19.[189,1398,265,1323]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 11. Haplodrassus medes sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (MHNG). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B–D, H. Palp, ventral, retrolateral, proventral and retroventral views. E–G. Bulb, proventral, dorsal and retroventral views. I. Apical portion of bulb, retroventral view. J. Chelicerae, posterior view. Abbreviations: Bb = bulge of bulb; Ea = embolic apophysis. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B–C, F, J = 0.2 mm; D, H–I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4906037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4906037/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">Fig. 11B, E</figureCitation>
), and by the shape of the tibial apophysis, relatively sharp and straight (vs with indentations or sharper).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="86" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,324,955,981]" box="[189,324,955,981]" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,955,981]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="86" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,955,981]" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,1399,1002,1063]" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">
The specific epithet is a noun in apposition and refers to the ancient group of Iranian people who inhabited an area known as Media between western and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[841,892,1037,1063]" name="Iran" pageId="18" pageNumber="86">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
